<br>
Total:43 cards(40 non-Magi)   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The main idea behind the deck, is to use Harmony to get almost everyones creatures down to or up to 3,  use LIFEWEAVE or TUK BERRIES to add energy to Weave Hyren and then using your Weave Hyren&#39;s effect of WILD GROWTH that will add at least one energy to each of your weave creatures. Now if you use LIFEWEAVE that will add 3 energy to all other weaves creatures.<br>
<br>
Now your best bet is to start with Quirle and get TUK BERRIES right off in the beggining and save that for later.PLay some creatures use his ability to add 1 energy to a creature at the beggining of each players turn. After Quirle gets knocked off, Use either Kesia or Gia, personally I prefer to use Kesia and that way  I can use SAWGRASS for 3 energy to knock of some of the opponents tougher creatures and if by that time your still duking it out and have lost Kesia, Bring out Gia, with GIA&#39;S TOME, WEAVE HYREN and BUNGALOO. Now the smart idea would be to play GIA&#39;S TOME, TUK BERRIES, and any other relics you might have in your hand. Then play HARMONY, then play a WEAVE HYREN, and if you have them in your hand a PAGAJACK and a ARITEX. use ARITEX&#39;s power of HEAL and discard the PAGAJACK. So that next turn your Magi starts at starting energy instead of 0 and you energize still. Then from there use TUK BERRIES and LIFEWEAVE to add energy to WEAVE HYREN which in turn adds energy to all of your other weave creatures. BEAM OF LIGHT is in there to get rid of any pesky relics that might be a thorn in your side, The &quot;Ummm...No!&quot; is prevent any cards from discarding your WEAVE Hyren from play. The RAYJES stuff is in there to prevent underneath cards from burrowing and  the cloak is make sure all of your cards can defend and attack. Also to make sure that your GRASS HYREN can use its effect EVADE and WEAVE HUTS effect SHELTER. UWAMAR BEADS are nice cuz if someone plans on making you discard cards you can search your deck and pull out one  weave creature and play it for full energy without paying any cost. TOMORROW&#39;S JEWEL is just there to help speed up the process of searching through your deck for the cards you need. MIRROR PENDANT i&#39;m sure could be useful depeding on times. I&#39;m sure the purpose of the JUNJERTRUG HORN is pretty obvious so yeah. <br>
<br>
Well this is my first try at a decent weave deck, it worked well earlier. I&#39;m sure there are some changes that can be made that will make the deck stronger, but for the cards I have this works well. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
